South Africa's flanker Siya Kolisi lifts the Webb Ellis Cup as they celebrate winning the Japan 2019 Rugby World Cup final match between England and South Africa at the International Stadium Yokohama in Yokohama on November 2, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - Daily Show host Trevor Noah has congratulated South Africa's Springboks after they beat England in the Rugby World Cup final on Saturday. READ: South Africa defeat England to win third Rugby World Cup The South African born comedian and talk show host said on twitter - Springboks are back on top of the world. Well done Bokke. You have made us all proud. The Bokke defeated England 32 -12 at the International Stadium Yokohama in Yokohama. Springbok captain Siya Kolisi thanked the South African fans after the game saying, "this is what we can do as a team when we decide on one goal and one dream. Thank you so much for everything." The Boks first won the Webb Ellis Cup in 1995 and again in 2007. WATCH: Ramaphosa's pep talk to the Boks This world cup win becomes the Boks' third championship crown, leaving them equal to New Zealand's All Blacks.